      • languageWords

        public java.util.ArrayList<StarlingWord> languageWords
        A language XML element is parsed into a list of objects of type StarlingWord.

        Example : <field name="TRK">gün 2, güneš 1, (dial.) gujaš 1</field>

        The XML element will be parsed into 3 objects of type StarlingWord (for the words gün, güneš and gujaš respectively).

      • buildWORDS

        public abstract java.lang.Integer buildWORDS(java.lang.Integer recordNr,
                                             java.lang.String elementName,
                                             java.lang.String elementValue)
        Description copied from interface: StarlingRDFModelBuilderI
        Action for any XML element with a name different from PROTO, MEANING, RUSMEAN or NUMBER. Target elements that should be processed are all elements that have a Starling language identifier (3 or 4 letter language code) as their name (e.g. TAT). These actually refer to cognates of the proto-form in the XML PROTO element. Build lemon lexical entries, etc.
        Specified by:
        buildWORDS in interface StarlingRDFModelBuilderI
        Parameters:
        recordNr - XML recordnr
        elementName - XML element name
        elementValue - XML element value (String)
        Returns:
        status
